00:52:31.330 --> 00:52:31.750
KENNY WERNER: No.

00:52:31.750 --> 00:52:33.580
AUDIENCE: --and then
you started enjoying it?

00:52:33.580 --> 00:52:36.015
KENNY WERNER: No, but after I
started, they made me continue.

00:52:36.015 --> 00:52:36.640
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:52:36.640 --> 00:52:37.227
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:37.227 --> 00:52:38.810
KENNY WERNER: It was
my idea to start,

00:52:38.810 --> 00:52:40.393
but after that, they
made me continue.

00:52:40.393 --> 00:52:44.080
Because they saw
a talent, I guess.

00:52:44.080 --> 00:52:46.420
I started because I went
to a friend's birthday.

00:52:46.420 --> 00:52:49.172
His father was playing piano
in the middle of the room.

00:52:49.172 --> 00:52:51.130
And I had never saw a
piano played live before,

00:52:51.130 --> 00:52:53.410
and I was like, spellbound.

00:52:53.410 --> 00:52:54.640
I was like, wow!

00:52:54.640 --> 00:52:56.620
Not only that, I was
really noticing how

00:52:56.620 --> 00:52:58.510
he was the center of attention

00:52:58.510 --> 00:52:59.470
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:59.470 --> 00:53:01.030
And that was very
attractive to me.

00:53:01.030 --> 00:53:02.030
[LAUGHTER]

00:53:02.030 --> 00:53:06.160
So I went home, and I
said, Mom, get me a piano.

00:53:06.160 --> 00:53:08.510
And to tell you the
truth, though, I sat down,

00:53:08.510 --> 00:53:10.630
and I could plunk out
songs I heard on the radio.

00:53:10.630 --> 00:53:11.670
And I went back
into the kitchen,

00:53:11.670 --> 00:53:13.060
and I said, good
news, Mom, I won't

00:53:13.060 --> 00:53:14.351
be needing those piano lessons.

00:53:14.351 --> 00:53:15.820
I already figured
out how to play.

00:53:15.820 --> 00:53:16.540
[LAUGHTER]

00:53:16.540 --> 00:53:19.259
And I've actually
believed that ever since.

00:53:19.259 --> 00:53:19.759
[LAUGHTER]

00:53:19.759 --> 00:53:21.208
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:53:24.589 --> 00:53:26.690
AUDIENCE: Hi, my
name is Frances Lao.

00:53:26.690 --> 00:53:28.610
I'm also from OSA.

00:53:28.610 --> 00:53:32.942
Is jazz the only genre you play?

00:53:32.942 --> 00:53:33.650
KENNY WERNER: No.

00:53:33.650 --> 00:53:37.220
I don't really-- this is crazy,
but I don't really consider

00:53:37.220 --> 00:53:38.750
myself a jazz musician.

00:53:38.750 --> 00:53:40.160
I learned that language.

00:53:40.160 --> 00:53:43.760
It's a very colorful language,
very hip rhythm, and harmony,

00:53:43.760 --> 00:53:44.990
and melodies.

00:53:44.990 --> 00:53:49.790
But in my mind, I
think my actual best

00:53:49.790 --> 00:53:50.780
job would have been--

00:53:50.780 --> 00:53:52.040
and may still happen--

00:53:52.040 --> 00:53:53.900
scoring movies.

00:53:53.900 --> 00:53:55.340
Because I play very visually.

00:53:55.340 --> 00:53:56.970
I always have a visual in mind.

00:53:56.970 --> 00:53:59.230
It's just that when
I came out of school,

00:53:59.230 --> 00:54:02.000
I didn't pursue
specifically what I wanted.

00:54:02.000 --> 00:54:04.370
And jazz musicians
called me for gigs,

00:54:04.370 --> 00:54:07.820
so 10 years later, I found
myself being a jazz musician.

00:54:07.820 --> 00:54:11.180
But I did play some
classical music.

00:54:11.180 --> 00:54:14.930
I love old '60s and '70s rock.

00:54:14.930 --> 00:54:17.220
I actually think
before I learned jazz,

00:54:17.220 --> 00:54:19.130
I was more like an
Elton John or something.

00:54:19.130 --> 00:54:20.590
I liked to play
that way, you know?

00:54:20.590 --> 00:54:21.980
And I still love that.

00:54:21.980 --> 00:54:26.590
But it's just that jazz an very
accessible language to me now,

00:54:26.590 --> 00:54:28.640
and it's a very
interesting language.

00:54:28.640 --> 00:54:31.905
So I guess that's what
I ended up mostly doing.

00:54:31.905 --> 00:54:33.280
I'm actually trying
to get away--

00:54:33.280 --> 00:54:34.910
in my own mind--
get away from the--

00:54:34.910 --> 00:54:36.620
I like to think of it
as improvised music

00:54:36.620 --> 00:54:41.940
rather than jazz, which
suggests a whole mindset.

00:54:41.940 --> 00:54:42.490
OK?

00:54:42.490 --> 00:54:42.740
Yeah?

00:54:42.740 --> 00:54:43.573
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:54:43.573 --> 00:54:45.419
KENNY WERNER: You're welcome.

